There is an image in Leibniz's Theodicy of a "square tower", which from a distance is deceptively seen by the eyes as being round, as its edges are imperceptible to the sense of sight. It's easy to imagine a Zen style martial artist monk meditating on it as a spiritual practice.

"Visualize the tower... Focus on how its edges appear as it gets nearer and its true square form reveals itself... See the illusion in all things and remember to always look for their true image... An enemy will always first appear as a round tower... To defeat him, you need..."
